init_text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf totally didn't know what to make of this house.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So he decided to wait it out, and sure enough, after three months of sitting there the little pig came out.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The little pig came out, looked around, and went right back into the house.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: He found a laser gun so powerful that it could even cut through steel, let alone uranium.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The wolf went searching for a way to get around the laser defense shield and ended up finding a grenade launcher.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The story of Pig number 92 was written by a famous piggy poet.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: This story was written to teach children the power of education.
